assignee: codex-root
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "Every REST command reaches the live API through the supported Undici contract; typed WebSocket target helpers match current Home Assistant response fields and expose triggers, conditions, and services; setup wizard and global settings validate against the local instance without persisting private data in the repository; all formats, help paths, unit/coverage/release gates, and live read-only E2E checks pass; reviewed PR is merged and verified on master"
definition_of_ready: "Official API docs, complete pm inventory, current code, and live failure evidence reviewed"
value: A reliable agent-first CLI that works against current Home Assistant rather than only mocked tests
impact: Restores all REST functionality and improves deterministic target discovery for automation agents
outcome: Current Home Assistant can be discovered and operated safely through typed and passthrough CLI surfaces
why_now: Undici 8 currently makes every REST command fail before network I/O
